07/04/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A regional meeting of the Disaster Preparedness and Prevention Initiative (DPPI) in Southeast Europe begins in Sarajevo on Tuesday (April 7th). 
Representatives of ministries and institutions from Macedonia, Albania, BiH, Bulgaria, Moldova, Romania, Slovenia, Serbia, Montenegro and Croatia will attend, as will representatives of the EU, NATO and the International Red Cross. 
The DPPI is an initiative of the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe and aims to boost regional co-operation in preventing fires, floods and earthquakes. 
(DPPI web site, MIA - 06/04/09)
